WEBVTT

00:57.491 --> 01:00.459
[singing in foreign language]

01:24.185 --> 01:26.151
[motor engine turns over]

01:28.622 --> 01:31.623
[screaming]

01:31.625 --> 01:34.626
[instrumental music]

01:50.111 --> 01:52.544
<i>Reporter 1: Christian community</i>
<i> has become a soft target</i>

01:52.546 --> 01:55.114
<i> for radical groups</i>
<i> in the last one month.</i>

01:57.418 --> 01:58.984
<i> Reporter 2: This incident</i>
<i> has left</i>

01:58.986 --> 02:01.220
<i> many in the Christian</i>
<i> minority community</i>

02:01.222 --> 02:04.089
<i> shattered and broken.</i>
<i> We just hope that the...</i>

02:04.091 --> 02:06.625
<i> Reporter 3: One hundred and</i>
<i> twenty seven church buildings</i>

02:06.627 --> 02:10.429
<i> have been torn down or burned.</i>

02:10.431 --> 02:12.764
<i>Tens of thousands of Christians</i>
<i> have hidden</i>

02:12.766 --> 02:15.167
<i> in the surrounding forests</i>
<i> for months.</i>

02:15.169 --> 02:17.469
<i>Reporter 4: We don't understand</i>
<i> that if India is called</i>

02:17.471 --> 02:21.974
<i> a secular state,</i>
<i> why do such incidents happen?</i>

02:21.976 --> 02:26.011
<i> Reporter 5: [indistinct]</i>
<i> to defend itself.</i>

02:26.013 --> 02:28.780
<i> Christians alleged that</i>
<i> right wing organization...</i>

02:28.782 --> 02:31.750
[indistinct shouting]

03:01.649 --> 03:04.883
- Guess who.
- An ugly old hag.

03:04.885 --> 03:06.051
- Manav.
- Ow!

03:06.053 --> 03:07.419
Shh.

03:09.223 --> 03:11.590
- Look.
- Oh.

03:19.133 --> 03:21.533
Shanti: "Thank you for your
submission of your work."

03:28.342 --> 03:31.043
<i> Manav: There were a lot</i>
<i> of things I didn't know</i>

03:31.045 --> 03:34.146
<i> when Shanti,</i>
<i> who was heavily pregnant,</i>

03:34.148 --> 03:38.383
<i> and I came to Orissa.</i>

03:38.385 --> 03:41.720
<i> Back then,</i>
<i> the thing I was most afraid of</i>

03:41.722 --> 03:43.989
<i> was the curse of leprosy.</i>

03:43.991 --> 03:48.026
<i> But at that moment, it seemed</i>
<i> like the obvious choice.</i>

03:48.028 --> 03:49.861
<i> I needed a remote location,</i>

03:49.863 --> 03:53.398
<i> I had a job offer of sorts,</i>

03:53.400 --> 03:55.934
<i> and I understood the language.</i>

03:55.936 --> 03:57.936
[train horn blares]

04:05.212 --> 04:08.180
<i> The conversion issue was hot.</i>

04:08.182 --> 04:11.817
<i> All perfect for a journalist</i>
<i> who had a point to make.</i>

04:26.033 --> 04:28.700
- Banerjee?
- Dilip?

04:31.472 --> 04:34.406
- Prishima told me about you.
- We've been waiting for you.

04:34.408 --> 04:36.308
- That's my wife.
-<i> Namaskar. Namaskar.</i>

04:36.310 --> 04:38.977
-<i> Namaskar. </i>
- Uh, look, here the keys.

04:38.979 --> 04:42.414
Ah, thank you.
And here's the rent.

04:42.416 --> 04:44.750
- Five hundred. Here.
- Ah, thank you.

04:44.752 --> 04:47.152
- Thank you.
- Uh...

04:47.154 --> 04:48.787
- Banerjee?
- Yeah.

04:48.789 --> 04:50.989
Deposit?

04:50.991 --> 04:54.293
- Uh...
- It's just one month rent.

04:54.295 --> 04:57.162
We didn't know of the deposit.

04:57.164 --> 04:59.064
But I guess, uh...

05:00.467 --> 05:04.136
- Um, h-- here's the 500.
- Mm-hmm.

05:04.138 --> 05:06.571
I've arranged the rickshaw.
He knows the place.

05:06.573 --> 05:08.140
- Okay. Good.
- Thank you.

05:08.142 --> 05:09.541
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

05:15.282 --> 05:16.548
[sighs]

05:19.620 --> 05:21.586
All we can afford.

05:25.693 --> 05:27.993
It's fine. I know.

05:35.669 --> 05:38.170
Shanti: Are you gonna see
the editor tomorrow?

05:38.172 --> 05:40.706
Manav: Yeah, I need the work.

05:40.708 --> 05:42.774
You'll get it.

05:42.776 --> 05:45.711
You're a great writer.

05:45.713 --> 05:48.980
And then... promotions.

05:48.982 --> 05:51.616
Editor. Best-selling author.

05:59.893 --> 06:02.894
[indistinct chatter]

06:12.740 --> 06:14.973
Manav Banerjee?
[speaks in foreign language]

06:29.189 --> 06:32.491
- I like your work, Banerjee.
- Thank you, sir.

06:32.493 --> 06:37.229
But to give you full-time,
I need new material.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.265
Raj.

06:40.267 --> 06:41.733
- Hm.
- I-- I can produce, sir.

06:41.735 --> 06:43.602
It's just that my wife
is pregnant, so...

06:43.604 --> 06:46.772
- Oh. First child?
- Yes, sir.

06:46.774 --> 06:48.774
- How long you've been married?
- Not long, sir.

06:48.776 --> 06:52.344
Aha. Pregnant already.

06:52.346 --> 06:53.678
Yeah.

06:53.680 --> 06:57.015
I'll see what I can do.
So, right then.

07:02.890 --> 07:04.890
Sir, what kind of article
are you looking for?

07:04.892 --> 07:06.224
News.

07:06.226 --> 07:08.427
Sir, yesterday
at Baripada Market,

07:08.429 --> 07:10.529
<i> a young beggar boy</i>
<i> was found to have leprosy.</i>

07:10.531 --> 07:11.963
<i> People were shouting,</i>
<i> pushing each other,</i>

07:11.965 --> 07:13.732
<i> wondering what to do</i>
<i> with the boy.</i>

07:13.734 --> 07:15.534
<i> And then from the crowd</i>
<i> walked a man.</i>

07:15.536 --> 07:16.735
Okay.

07:16.737 --> 07:18.403
[indistinct chatter]

07:18.405 --> 07:20.238
Come on, it's okay.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.808
[indistinct chatter]

07:22.810 --> 07:26.244
Manav... who is he?

07:26.246 --> 07:28.580
Staines. Not news.

07:28.582 --> 07:30.682
- Oh. Someone told you?
- No.

07:32.719 --> 07:36.087
He's a missionary, Banerjee.

07:36.089 --> 07:38.256
You said it yourself.

07:38.258 --> 07:41.993
First, conversions,
then imperialism.

07:41.995 --> 07:43.061
You want to support that?

07:43.063 --> 07:44.796
[telephone ringing]

07:44.798 --> 07:46.064
Mm.

07:47.968 --> 07:50.735
Hello. No, I'm busy now.

07:56.310 --> 07:57.509
Sir.

07:58.846 --> 08:00.078
Do you know how much it costs

08:00.080 --> 08:03.014
to convert someone
to Christianity?

08:03.016 --> 08:06.351
Five hundred among the poor.
Ten dollars.

08:06.353 --> 08:08.553
Less, I think, if the convert
happens to be a leper.

08:10.991 --> 08:12.424
So?

08:12.426 --> 08:13.959
Sir, a missionary flies back
to the West

08:13.961 --> 08:15.994
and tells them
that he's converted 1000 people,

08:15.996 --> 08:17.462
for which, of course,
he gets paid,

08:17.464 --> 08:20.966
but which is much more
than $10 per person.

08:20.968 --> 08:22.667
[chuckles] Good business.

08:22.669 --> 08:24.836
Yes. But the law here
in Orissa states that

08:24.838 --> 08:27.472
no person shall convert
or attempt to convert any person

08:27.474 --> 08:29.541
from one religious faith
to another.

08:29.543 --> 08:33.278
Yes, by use of force
or by inducement

08:33.280 --> 08:35.580
or by any fraudulent means.

08:37.651 --> 08:41.486
Sir, and yet not one missionary
has been charged.

08:41.488 --> 08:45.290
Not yet.
That would make good news, sir.

08:45.292 --> 08:48.260
[dramatic music]

08:55.168 --> 08:58.904
You bring me evidence
of illegal conversion

08:58.906 --> 09:01.406
by Graham Staines.

09:01.408 --> 09:03.642
I'll give you
a permanent position.

09:03.644 --> 09:06.411
Loan me a camera, sir,
and I'll get you photo evidence.

09:08.882 --> 09:12.050
I'll loan you a camera, but...

09:12.052 --> 09:14.085
I need a deposit.

09:14.087 --> 09:15.987
How much money do you have?

09:15.989 --> 09:17.956
[telephone ringing]

09:19.493 --> 09:20.759
Hello.

09:20.761 --> 09:22.994
I told you I am busy.

09:24.364 --> 09:25.997
No, I don't know anybody!

09:25.999 --> 09:27.866
Why do you have security
in this office?

09:27.868 --> 09:29.935
He's mad! Send him out!

09:31.038 --> 09:33.238
Mad fool.

09:33.240 --> 09:34.940
Dead is dead.

09:41.281 --> 09:43.682
This will do.

09:43.684 --> 09:45.850
There's a conversion
of a tribal girl

09:45.852 --> 09:47.652
in Baripada tomorrow.

09:49.856 --> 09:52.057
This is your opportunity.

09:52.059 --> 09:53.792
You won't be disappointed, sir.

09:53.794 --> 09:56.595
[horn honking]

09:56.597 --> 09:58.630
[speaking in foreign language]

10:00.400 --> 10:01.566
Ticket. Where you go?

10:01.568 --> 10:03.802
Uh, I'm from New Orissa.

10:03.804 --> 10:05.070
I'm a journalist.

10:05.072 --> 10:07.572
[chuckles]

10:07.574 --> 10:10.208
L-- listen,
can I pay you tomorrow?

10:10.210 --> 10:11.977
No.

10:11.979 --> 10:14.446
Listen, my wife is pregnant.
I need to get home.

10:14.448 --> 10:16.214
- Congratulations.
- Please.

10:16.216 --> 10:18.183
[speaking in foreign language]

10:20.220 --> 10:22.587
Do you want me
to write about your bus?

10:22.589 --> 10:24.489
Halfway to BP Town,
this bus will be packed

10:24.491 --> 10:27.392
like cattle going to slaughter,
way beyond the seat limits.

10:27.394 --> 10:30.462
Do you want to lose
your license?

10:30.464 --> 10:31.730
[blows whistles]

10:31.732 --> 10:34.232
[whistles]

10:34.234 --> 10:36.201
[grunting]

10:40.140 --> 10:42.140
[speaking in foreign language]

10:47.014 --> 10:49.014
I'm not getting out.

10:51.852 --> 10:53.385
Thank you.

10:54.688 --> 10:56.087
Baripada.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.991
[horn honking]

11:06.667 --> 11:08.066
[blows whistle]

11:16.376 --> 11:18.376
[speaking in foreign language]

11:20.781 --> 11:22.480
- Going to Baripada?
- Yes.

11:22.482 --> 11:25.450
[indistinct chatter]

11:29.956 --> 11:31.923
- Your bottle?
- Yes.

11:34.061 --> 11:35.493
Have it.

11:35.495 --> 11:38.163
All Indians
are brothers and sisters.

11:38.165 --> 11:42.033
Yes, all Indians
are my bothers and sisters.

11:42.035 --> 11:43.468
India is my country,

11:43.470 --> 11:46.204
and all Indians
are my brothers and sisters.

11:46.206 --> 11:48.173
I love my country,
and I'm proud

11:48.175 --> 11:50.308
of its rich and varied heritage.

11:50.310 --> 11:53.178
I shall always strive
to be worthy of it.

11:53.180 --> 11:57.482
I shall give my parents,
teachers and all elders respect

11:57.484 --> 12:00.085
and greet everyone
with courtesy.

12:00.087 --> 12:03.822
To my country and my people,
I pledge my devotion.

12:03.824 --> 12:05.256
- I am not.
- He's a leper!

12:05.258 --> 12:06.891
- I am cured.
Manav: Leper! He's a leper!

12:06.893 --> 12:08.927
- I am cured.
Manav: Stop the bus! Stop!

12:08.929 --> 12:11.429
- I am cured.
Manav: Stop!

12:11.431 --> 12:12.697
Sundar: I am cured!

12:12.699 --> 12:14.899
[retching]

12:17.237 --> 12:18.636
[blows whistle]

12:21.875 --> 12:24.876
Hey! Hey, stop, hey!

12:24.878 --> 12:28.580
Hey, stop the bus!
Stop the bus!

12:28.582 --> 12:30.582
I'll report you!

12:34.454 --> 12:36.688
Sundar: Please. Please.

12:38.058 --> 12:40.125
Please. Please.

12:46.566 --> 12:49.534
[speaking in foreign language]

13:33.780 --> 13:36.247
- Huh.
-<i> Namaskar.</i>

13:36.249 --> 13:38.183
<i> Namaskar.</i>

13:38.185 --> 13:40.418
Are you heading
towards Baripada Town?

13:40.420 --> 13:42.620
- Yup.
- I need to get home.

13:42.622 --> 13:44.823
Well, jump in. I won't bite.

13:56.703 --> 13:58.169
Sundar.

14:00.607 --> 14:03.875
You haven't mentioned
your visit.

14:03.877 --> 14:07.212
No good,<i> sahibo. </i>
How many times do I go?

14:07.214 --> 14:09.881
Graham: Seven times seventy.
- Leper! He's a leper!

14:09.883 --> 14:11.449
- Mate, mate, mate.
- Stop the car!

14:11.451 --> 14:13.518
- Just stop the car!
- He's alright. Calm down!

14:13.520 --> 14:15.987
- Stop the car! Stop!
- Alright, alright. Calm down.

14:15.989 --> 14:18.022
Manav: Stop this car now.

14:25.632 --> 14:28.032
I-- is this a setup?
He pays for my ticket.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.734
The bus leaves,
you turn up, huh?

14:29.736 --> 14:32.403
- Just offering you a lift.
- Not with a leper!

14:32.405 --> 14:35.340
Calm down, mate.
He's been healed 30 years.

14:35.342 --> 14:37.342
Whatever!
I can't travel with him! I--

14:37.344 --> 14:39.310
He's not contagious.
He's been healed.

14:39.312 --> 14:41.279
I can't! I...

15:09.776 --> 15:11.009
[yawns]

15:12.245 --> 15:14.245
[dogs barking at distance]

15:27.060 --> 15:29.027
I got the job.

15:30.063 --> 15:33.364
Wow, that's great.

15:33.366 --> 15:35.633
I have a story to cover.

15:43.877 --> 15:46.611
Do you want to be my bodyguard?

15:46.613 --> 15:48.846
[chuckles] Mm.

15:50.317 --> 15:52.617
- I've been...
- What?

15:54.220 --> 15:56.487
Nothing.
I just couldn't sleep.

15:57.624 --> 15:59.624
I'll sleep now.

16:05.565 --> 16:08.533
[singing in foreign language]

16:21.114 --> 16:24.082
[dramatic music]

16:27.654 --> 16:29.988
Are you willing to be baptized
of your own free will?

16:29.990 --> 16:31.022
Yes.

16:31.024 --> 16:32.523
David: I am the way, the truth,

16:32.525 --> 16:33.958
and the life.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.360
No one comes to the Father,

16:35.362 --> 16:36.828
except through me.

16:36.830 --> 16:38.696
I baptize you
in the name of the Father

16:38.698 --> 16:40.865
the Son, and the Holy Ghost.

17:03.890 --> 17:06.858
May the peace of God, which
passeth all understanding--

17:10.130 --> 17:11.997
Hey!

17:11.998 --> 17:13.865
- What do you have there?
- Good morning. May I help you?

17:13.867 --> 17:17.035
- Is it money? Huh?
- No, it's not.

17:17.037 --> 17:18.870
Th-- this is
an illegal conversion, huh?

17:18.872 --> 17:22.006
- No. Her mother is a Christian.
- Well, her father is a Hindu.

17:22.008 --> 17:24.475
He let her choose.

17:24.477 --> 17:27.979
- I want to talk to her.
- You can talk to me, sir.

17:27.981 --> 17:29.647
Where's your affidavit
for a conversion?

17:29.649 --> 17:32.817
If the police wants it,
I'll do it. You don't need it.

17:32.819 --> 17:35.987
You-- you think th-- this thing,
this-- this cross--

17:35.989 --> 17:37.088
- Let it go.
- Gives you the right?

17:37.090 --> 17:38.322
Don't touch. Let it go.

17:38.324 --> 17:39.924
You can do
any illegal conversion?

17:39.926 --> 17:41.526
- You can do what you like, huh?
- Who are you to ask?

17:41.528 --> 17:43.061
- This is not done!
- Let it go!

17:43.063 --> 17:45.163
I know people like you!
I want the papers!

17:45.165 --> 17:47.265
[indistinct shouting]

17:47.267 --> 17:48.733
[grunts]

17:50.403 --> 17:52.403
[indistinct chatter]

17:54.441 --> 17:56.441
[dramatic music]

17:58.044 --> 17:59.343
Hey.

18:03.917 --> 18:06.951
Hey, mister! Wait!

18:06.953 --> 18:08.853
It's not over yet!

18:12.692 --> 18:15.660
[upbeat music]

18:25.905 --> 18:27.872
[screaming]

18:31.911 --> 18:33.945
[speaking in foreign language]

18:47.727 --> 18:49.694
[cows mooing]

19:02.675 --> 19:05.676
[speaking in foreign language]

19:06.913 --> 19:09.247
[Shanti screaming]

19:09.249 --> 19:12.216
[singing in foreign language]

19:23.129 --> 19:26.097
[speaking in foreign language]

19:30.170 --> 19:32.336
[baby cooing]

19:34.874 --> 19:36.707
She's beautiful.

19:38.144 --> 19:39.877
Just like you.

19:41.347 --> 19:44.916
- Why didn't you tell me?
- A month early.

19:47.020 --> 19:48.853
Thought it was nothing.

19:48.855 --> 19:51.856
[indistinct chatter]

19:51.858 --> 19:53.858
You better pay them.

19:55.995 --> 19:58.963
[singing in foreign language]

20:15.848 --> 20:18.649
- Sir. Sir, one thing.
- Yeah, your fee, right?

20:18.651 --> 20:21.352
- No, no. Your wife.
- Yeah?

20:21.354 --> 20:23.888
She's bleeding.
Bleeding very much.

20:23.890 --> 20:25.389
Take her to hospital.

20:25.391 --> 20:28.392
[mellow music]

20:31.030 --> 20:32.997
[baby crying]

20:40.273 --> 20:43.207
I've made her comfortable.

20:43.209 --> 20:46.544
The uterus should contract now.

20:46.546 --> 20:50.214
But she has lost a lot of blood.
Too much.

20:50.216 --> 20:52.683
And if she continues to bleed...

20:52.685 --> 20:54.151
You understand?

21:06.366 --> 21:07.865
<i> Mishra: You want pay?</i>

21:07.867 --> 21:10.868
Manav: Sir, I need the money,
sir, so I...

21:10.870 --> 21:13.271
I'm sorry, Banerjee.
We have rules.

21:13.273 --> 21:14.705
Sir, I was attacked, sir.

21:14.707 --> 21:16.107
They didn't want to be
photographed, sir.

21:16.109 --> 21:18.042
Still, your responsibility.

21:18.044 --> 21:19.910
Sir, my wife is in hospital.
I've borrowed money

21:19.912 --> 21:21.245
to pay for medication
and blood, sir.

21:21.247 --> 21:23.648
I'm sorry,
that's your family matter.

21:25.084 --> 21:26.450
Sir.

21:28.488 --> 21:29.787
Mm.

21:31.324 --> 21:33.758
- At least this is good.
- Thank you, sir.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.092
[speaking in foreign language]

21:35.094 --> 21:38.062
[dramatic music]

21:42.568 --> 21:44.535
[speaking in foreign language]

21:46.339 --> 21:48.339
Good afternoon, sir.

21:50.143 --> 21:52.243
Yes, I think I have.

21:56.249 --> 21:57.715
He's good.

22:06.326 --> 22:09.860
Evidence of fraudulent
conversions by Staines

22:09.862 --> 22:12.997
are not easily come by.

22:12.999 --> 22:15.633
Sir, inducements
come in many forms, so...

22:15.635 --> 22:18.469
For success in an endeavor
like this,

22:18.471 --> 22:20.838
someone needs to become
a Christian

22:20.840 --> 22:23.708
in order to gain their trust.

22:23.710 --> 22:26.610
Thereby gather
the necessary evidence.

22:26.612 --> 22:28.612
Enough to use in a court of law.

22:30.616 --> 22:34.018
An endeavor worthy of support,
don't you think, Kedar?

22:34.020 --> 22:35.619
Certainly, sir.

22:39.058 --> 22:42.693
Of course, the person
who does this

22:42.695 --> 22:45.029
will have contact with lepers.

22:45.031 --> 22:47.231
[indistinct shouting]

22:51.504 --> 22:54.905
That means a bath every hour.
Uh-huh.

22:54.907 --> 22:56.907
[chuckles]

23:03.049 --> 23:06.817
Leprosy is the veil
behind which Staines operates.

23:06.819 --> 23:09.220
<i> The tool he uses.</i>

23:09.222 --> 23:12.390
You may need to prove
your loyalty with conversion.

23:18.331 --> 23:21.165
You take this,
you go all the way.

23:26.272 --> 23:28.072
- Banerjee.
- Sir.

23:30.076 --> 23:33.544
- To help you get around.
- And to get to church on time.

23:33.546 --> 23:35.780
[laughs]

23:48.795 --> 23:51.529
- Have you thought of a name?
- No.

23:52.865 --> 23:54.632
I like Vardanuja.

23:55.868 --> 23:58.302
- Gift of life?
- Hm.

23:58.304 --> 23:59.503
Hm.

24:07.213 --> 24:08.679
Vardanuja.

24:14.821 --> 24:16.821
[keys clacking]

24:31.904 --> 24:34.872
[indistinct chatter]

24:38.010 --> 24:41.011
[speaking in foreign language]

24:53.192 --> 24:56.193
[speaking in foreign language]

25:22.288 --> 25:24.889
- David?
- He gets too excited.

25:26.792 --> 25:28.659
Can't think you can push
a journalist around

25:28.661 --> 25:31.695
and get away with it.

25:31.697 --> 25:33.230
He means well.

25:33.232 --> 25:36.567
They have this law for a reason.

25:36.569 --> 25:40.037
'Cause there's people out there
not doing the right thing.

25:40.039 --> 25:42.039
We have to be above reproach.

25:44.210 --> 25:46.043
Fill out an FIR.

25:46.045 --> 25:47.611
[speaking in foreign language]

25:53.252 --> 25:56.921
- No point.
- I saw money change hands.

25:56.923 --> 26:00.724
Yeah, it happens every day,
every time you buy something.

26:00.726 --> 26:03.594
The Orissa Freedom
of Religion Act states that

26:03.596 --> 26:06.597
no person shall convert
or attempt to convert.

26:10.202 --> 26:11.635
You're right.

26:13.339 --> 26:15.205
But David, he suffers
the same disappointments

26:15.207 --> 26:17.608
that you do
when people are bought.

26:17.610 --> 26:20.277
He gets frustrated.

26:20.279 --> 26:23.514
We can't make any mistakes.

26:23.516 --> 26:26.750
Somebody's always going
to be trying to take this land.

26:26.752 --> 26:28.452
If that happens...

26:29.855 --> 26:31.822
who's gonna look after the home?

26:33.125 --> 26:35.159
Who's gonna defend them?

26:36.262 --> 26:37.628
Sundar?

26:39.365 --> 26:41.999
Misayel and Padma?

26:47.273 --> 26:49.273
No one would listen to David.

26:51.277 --> 26:52.810
I know.

26:54.280 --> 26:56.046
We must pray.

27:06.125 --> 27:08.092
Were you given any money?

27:08.094 --> 27:09.793
You are not registered
as a Christian.

27:09.795 --> 27:11.462
My mother is a Christian.

27:11.464 --> 27:13.664
But your father was not.

27:13.666 --> 27:16.667
- Sir, see, sir. Made to sign.
- It's just ownership.

27:16.669 --> 27:18.235
No, it's conversion.

27:18.237 --> 27:20.471
The affidavit
was not submitted

27:20.473 --> 27:22.339
and the conversion
was not registered.

27:22.341 --> 27:25.409
I will do the paperwork, sir.
I will.

27:25.411 --> 27:26.977
Woman 1: Now you get back
to work.

27:26.979 --> 27:28.912
Don't think you can take
any more liberties. Come!

27:28.914 --> 27:30.781
Half the day's gone
and nobody has done anything.

27:30.783 --> 27:33.484
Is that it?

27:33.486 --> 27:35.319
I can have you arrested
for assault.

27:35.321 --> 27:38.088
He broke my camera!

27:38.090 --> 27:40.057
Fill out an FIR.

27:44.630 --> 27:46.430
Sir, Manav.

27:46.432 --> 27:49.466
Mishra: Banerjee? Banerjee,
what have you been doing?

27:49.468 --> 27:51.502
We are paying you to convert.

27:51.504 --> 27:53.037
Sir, but I cannot convert
immediately.

27:53.039 --> 27:55.706
- That will be suspicious, so...
Mishra: Of course.

27:55.708 --> 27:58.709
But why are you making enemies
among Christians?

27:58.711 --> 28:01.979
I know what you've been doing.
Now leave the girl alone.

28:01.981 --> 28:03.347
Yes, sir.

28:07.053 --> 28:10.054
[instrumental music]

28:29.408 --> 28:32.743
- Do you know Staines?
- Of course.

28:32.745 --> 28:35.045
Is he into conversions?

28:35.047 --> 28:36.880
<i> Tries to convert you.</i>
<i> He gives you work</i>

28:36.882 --> 28:39.316
at the Leprosy Home.
That's inducement.

28:39.318 --> 28:41.852
<i> Man 1: I can make my own</i>
<i> decision about conversion.</i>

28:41.854 --> 28:44.254
No inducement brings
real conversion, anyway.

28:52.932 --> 28:55.666
One day I'll find the proof
of him converting the tribals.

29:09.048 --> 29:11.014
[indistinct chatter]

29:17.623 --> 29:19.456
[speaking in foreign language]
<i> Namaskar.</i>

29:21.460 --> 29:24.294
I buy from him and I sell.
Business, sir. Business.

29:30.970 --> 29:32.970
Did the church give you money
to become a Christian?

29:32.972 --> 29:36.707
No. Instead I give money
to church every month.

29:36.709 --> 29:38.475
My offering.

29:41.580 --> 29:44.648
As a fellow Rotarian, we believe
in service before self.

29:44.650 --> 29:47.317
<i> And Graham is no different.</i>

29:47.319 --> 29:49.953
He's taking care
of lots of people

29:49.955 --> 29:52.389
who are rejected
by their own people.

29:57.229 --> 30:00.197
[speaking in foreign language]

30:04.970 --> 30:07.004
[children chattering]

30:10.943 --> 30:13.310
Timothy: Let's go get dad.
Come on, quick, quick, quick.

30:13.312 --> 30:15.112
- No, you won't.
- Let's go get him.

30:15.114 --> 30:17.014
Whoa, whoa. Careful.

30:17.016 --> 30:18.515
Careful, careful.

30:18.517 --> 30:20.317
[shouting]

30:20.319 --> 30:22.319
[grunts]

30:22.321 --> 30:24.655
- Stop.
- Get him! Get him!

30:24.657 --> 30:26.690
- Stop, stop, stop.
- Hey, hey. Alright, come on.

30:26.692 --> 30:28.859
- I'm getting the book.
- Hey. Careful.

30:28.861 --> 30:30.761
What you reading?

30:32.932 --> 30:36.700
It's a great book
about a missionary.

30:36.702 --> 30:40.037
Can you read us some?

30:40.039 --> 30:42.139
I think you're gonna find it
quite boring.

30:42.141 --> 30:43.740
- Please?
- Please?

30:46.312 --> 30:50.380
"Missionaries constantly face
expendability."

30:50.382 --> 30:53.984
What does expendability mean?

30:53.986 --> 30:55.552
That's when somebody
does something

30:55.554 --> 30:58.689
somebody else thinks
doesn't matter.

30:58.691 --> 31:00.824
Why?

31:00.826 --> 31:03.393
Well, for us...

31:03.395 --> 31:06.396
it's because
they don't know God...

31:06.398 --> 31:08.232
because they're the ones
that don't realize

31:08.234 --> 31:12.069
that they're living lives
that have no eternal value.

31:14.340 --> 31:16.640
Can you read some of our books?

31:16.642 --> 31:18.242
[chuckles]

31:18.244 --> 31:21.211
[static on radio]

31:24.717 --> 31:26.884
Man on radio: In the series,
playing along

31:26.886 --> 31:29.253
with Sachin Tendulkar,
Sourav Ganguly

31:29.255 --> 31:31.688
and Mohammad Azharuddin.

31:31.690 --> 31:33.991
The news in detail.

31:33.993 --> 31:36.159
The general secretary
led the campaign

31:36.161 --> 31:38.195
against the Christian
missionaries

31:38.197 --> 31:41.865
whom he claims are converting
poor tribals illegally

31:41.867 --> 31:44.067
in so-called jungle camps.

31:44.069 --> 31:47.104
"Missionaries
do not belong here," he said.

31:47.106 --> 31:49.406
<i> The secretary demanded</i>
<i> that all missionaries</i>

31:49.408 --> 31:51.675
<i> be required</i>
<i> to leave India immediately</i>

31:51.677 --> 31:53.710
<i> for converting tribals</i>
<i> forcibly.</i>

31:53.712 --> 31:56.480
<i> He cited recent violence</i>
<i> against Christians...</i>

31:58.717 --> 32:00.684
[indistinct chatter]

32:07.526 --> 32:10.260
Ah, the man who chose to walk.

32:10.262 --> 32:12.796
<i> Namaskar.</i>

32:12.798 --> 32:16.199
- Must have been a long walk.
- [chuckles] Yes.

32:25.077 --> 32:27.744
[children chattering]

32:27.746 --> 32:29.713
Sorry
I couldn't give you a lift.

32:29.715 --> 32:30.814
No.

32:42.761 --> 32:44.394
So what can I do for you?

32:44.396 --> 32:47.331
- Oh, uh, I'm a journalist.
- Yup.

32:47.333 --> 32:51.101
And I-- I was amazed,
shocked, actually,

32:51.103 --> 32:53.503
to see you walk into that crowd
in the marketplace

32:53.505 --> 32:56.139
and physically pick up that boy.

32:57.843 --> 33:00.544
- Oh, that was nothing.
- No, but it was, really.

33:02.181 --> 33:06.116
Just a sick kid, mate.
It's really no big deal.

33:06.118 --> 33:08.585
- What's your name?
- Manav Banerjee.

33:11.457 --> 33:13.924
Graham Staines.
Nice to properly meet you.

33:13.926 --> 33:15.993
Yes.

33:15.995 --> 33:18.261
Write stories about the people
who really suffer

33:18.263 --> 33:20.430
in this society,
like that boy.

33:20.432 --> 33:21.932
Not about me.

33:24.103 --> 33:26.670
I-- I know
I didn't want the lift,

33:26.672 --> 33:29.339
but I'm still impressed
with the work you do.

33:29.341 --> 33:32.142
Then write about the work,
not about me.

33:32.144 --> 33:34.277
But it's your work, so...

33:34.279 --> 33:37.214
We'll talk about it
when I get back.

33:37.216 --> 33:39.716
Gotta go to a jungle camp.

33:39.718 --> 33:41.418
Christian gathering...

33:43.122 --> 33:45.088
for tribal people?

33:48.694 --> 33:51.628
Yeah.
It's out in Manoharpur village.

33:53.465 --> 33:55.432
Speak to you later.

34:01.707 --> 34:03.673
Man 2: All arrangements
are done. We're ready to go.

34:03.675 --> 34:05.208
Very good.

34:07.813 --> 34:09.646
Hi. Come on.

34:09.648 --> 34:12.616
[instrumental music]

34:32.271 --> 34:35.272
[speaking in foreign language]

35:03.268 --> 35:06.103
Give her a meal. She can't stay.

35:06.105 --> 35:09.106
[speaking in foreign language]

35:28.093 --> 35:30.060
You think I'm harsh?

35:34.633 --> 35:38.001
She keeps bringing alcohol
into the home.

35:38.003 --> 35:39.970
Lowers the effectiveness
of the medication.

35:39.972 --> 35:41.538
Can't allow that.

35:43.075 --> 35:45.442
She's not contagious, so...

35:45.444 --> 35:47.844
she can go back home
with her family.

35:47.846 --> 35:51.081
The village is not happy, so...

35:52.317 --> 35:54.484
There's a cure for leprosy now.

35:54.486 --> 35:56.453
About time they caught up.

35:56.455 --> 35:59.422
So, you won't help her anymore?

35:59.424 --> 36:01.424
No, I'm gonna help her, mate.

36:01.426 --> 36:04.327
And I am helping her.

36:04.329 --> 36:06.496
Getting her back home is
the best thing I can do for her.

36:06.498 --> 36:08.899
Look, you want a story, right?

36:11.436 --> 36:14.271
There's a story. Sundar.

36:14.273 --> 36:16.373
Hasn't had leprosy
for nearly 30 years

36:16.375 --> 36:17.941
and yet an educated man like you

36:17.943 --> 36:19.776
won't even ride
in the same vehicle with him.

36:19.778 --> 36:21.678
It's-- it's his karma.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.780
I couldn't risk that
on my baby and my wife.

36:23.782 --> 36:26.883
He's suffered enough
for his karma.

36:26.885 --> 36:28.885
He's dead, you know.

36:30.622 --> 36:33.623
It's true. He's dead.

36:33.625 --> 36:35.325
They performed
the death ceremony for him

36:35.327 --> 36:37.561
<i> back in his own village.</i>

36:37.563 --> 36:40.096
[mellow music]

36:42.634 --> 36:45.468
<i> I remember Sundar just...</i>

36:45.470 --> 36:48.738
<i> standing there like a ghost...</i>

36:48.740 --> 36:51.708
<i> saying over and over,</i>
<i> "I'm not dead.</i>

36:54.313 --> 36:55.912
I'm not dead."

36:57.683 --> 36:59.883
You should talk to him.

37:02.721 --> 37:04.254
Manav: Mr. Staines.

37:06.325 --> 37:08.825
What motivates you?

37:08.827 --> 37:10.927
No articles about me, right?

37:10.929 --> 37:14.497
Do you hope the lepers
will become Christians?

37:14.499 --> 37:16.967
- Of course.
- Hm.

37:18.370 --> 37:20.604
This is the man,<i> dada.</i>

37:20.606 --> 37:22.606
He is looking for evidence.

37:27.412 --> 37:29.512
[sighs]

37:32.284 --> 37:34.751
He's a journalist.

37:34.753 --> 37:37.420
He has a right to look.

37:37.422 --> 37:38.755
- Hey, dad.
- Hi, dad.

37:38.757 --> 37:40.423
Boys.

37:40.425 --> 37:42.292
This is Mr. Banerjee.

37:42.294 --> 37:43.760
-<i> Namaskar. </i>
-<i> Namaskar.</i>

37:43.762 --> 37:45.362
[chuckles]<i> Namaskar.</i>

37:45.364 --> 37:47.597
You're a good batsman.
How old are you now?

37:47.599 --> 37:49.566
I'm six years old.

37:49.568 --> 37:52.068
Ah, maybe someday you can play
for Australia.

37:52.070 --> 37:55.272
No, I want to play for India.
Like Sachin.

37:55.274 --> 37:57.807
- But you're from Australia.
- I'm from dust.

38:00.445 --> 38:04.948
Yes, you are. Now go on inside,
wash the dust off your hands.

38:04.950 --> 38:07.384
Get some lunch,
'cause we gotta go.

38:07.386 --> 38:09.352
- Mom!
- Mom! We won!

38:14.559 --> 38:17.627
Bible says God created us
from the dust of the Earth.

38:19.598 --> 38:21.331
Dust for dust.

38:24.269 --> 38:25.869
See you later.

38:35.247 --> 38:37.447
What? Maybe I'm just interested
in his work.

38:37.449 --> 38:40.650
Mm. And maybe you'll start
hugging lepers next.

38:45.424 --> 38:46.623
You ready to go to jungle camp?

38:46.625 --> 38:48.091
- Yeah.
- Mm?

38:50.128 --> 38:52.195
- Come.
- What did you say?

38:53.999 --> 38:56.866
- Oh.
- I want you to come with us.

38:56.868 --> 38:59.502
I have to stay and look after
Esther. But nice try.

39:01.106 --> 39:02.639
If you wanna take anything
to play with,

39:02.641 --> 39:04.808
better go get it now.

39:04.810 --> 39:06.142
- Okay.
- Uh-uh.

39:06.144 --> 39:08.778
Take your plate to the kitchen.

39:08.780 --> 39:10.113
Thank you.

39:14.786 --> 39:16.553
Oh.

39:16.555 --> 39:18.555
I'm gonna miss you too.

39:30.402 --> 39:32.135
<i> Namaskar.</i>

39:32.137 --> 39:33.870
<i> Namaskar.</i>

39:33.872 --> 39:36.539
Manav: It must be a...

39:36.541 --> 39:38.308
Must be difficult
bringing up your children

39:38.310 --> 39:40.543
here in India, huh?

39:40.545 --> 39:41.811
You're a journalist?

39:41.813 --> 39:43.346
Yes, I actually work
for "New..."

39:43.348 --> 39:44.814
Hm.

39:47.252 --> 39:49.619
Leave my children out of it.

40:06.905 --> 40:09.906
[man speaking
in foreign language]

40:37.369 --> 40:40.336
[singing in foreign language]

40:45.744 --> 40:48.711
[men speaking
in foreign language]

41:04.729 --> 41:06.162
[speaking in foreign language]

41:15.006 --> 41:17.841
[dramatic music]

42:08.393 --> 42:11.361
<i> Manav: I didn't know what</i>
<i> this man Mahendra was doing,</i>

42:11.363 --> 42:14.330
<i> but our paths</i>
<i> were about to cross.</i>

42:14.332 --> 42:17.467
<i> I decided to visit the village</i>
<i> of the woman</i>

42:17.469 --> 42:19.802
<i> whom Staines had sent away.</i>

42:19.804 --> 42:24.140
<i> Apparently, Mahendra had been</i>
<i> at work there.</i>

42:24.142 --> 42:27.110
[indistinct chatter]

42:58.343 --> 43:01.311
[instrumental music]

43:24.102 --> 43:27.537
What if you convert
to Christianity?

43:27.539 --> 43:29.639
Staines can help you,
protect you.

43:31.876 --> 43:34.978
- Not out here, sir.
- Surely.

43:34.980 --> 43:37.280
The village elders
will decide tonight, sir.

43:42.754 --> 43:45.722
[indistinct chatter]

44:08.647 --> 44:10.580
Your wife drew water
from the well.

44:10.582 --> 44:13.583
She wanted to save
the crop, sir.

44:13.585 --> 44:17.186
Don't you know it's expensive
to have the well purified?

44:19.758 --> 44:21.190
But she's cured, sir.

44:21.192 --> 44:23.626
How do we know
the curse is lifted?

44:23.628 --> 44:25.328
Because she's cured, sir.

44:25.330 --> 44:27.630
Maybe we are all under a curse.

44:27.632 --> 44:28.931
Because we have not dealt
properly

44:28.933 --> 44:30.933
with such people in the past.

44:30.935 --> 44:33.169
- Make him pay.
- Make him pay!

44:33.171 --> 44:35.338
[indistinct chatter]

44:37.275 --> 44:39.542
Unh-unh-unh. He cannot pay.

44:41.846 --> 44:44.213
Does anybody want him
to stay in the village?

44:48.286 --> 44:50.253
Will anyone speak for him?

44:55.994 --> 44:57.427
Manav: I will.

45:04.335 --> 45:05.902
[man speaks in foreign language]

45:05.904 --> 45:07.637
Manav:<i> Namaskar.</i>

45:07.639 --> 45:10.373
My name is Manav Banerjee.

45:10.375 --> 45:13.476
- I'm a journalist.
- He's not from the village.

45:16.047 --> 45:18.314
The government clinics
and hospitals provide medicines

45:18.316 --> 45:19.982
that heal other illnesses.

45:19.984 --> 45:22.652
You accept those treatments.
Then why not all?

45:24.422 --> 45:26.656
This one is working
for the missionaries.

45:26.658 --> 45:30.693
Mahendra, let him speak. Hmm.

45:30.695 --> 45:32.895
The government medicines
have cured her.

45:32.897 --> 45:34.530
They want him to take her back,
so--

45:34.532 --> 45:37.166
It was the missionaries
who said she was cured.

45:37.168 --> 45:39.335
So the government will agree
with the missionaries.

45:39.337 --> 45:41.170
[scoffs] Government.

45:41.172 --> 45:43.439
Government does
what the missionaries want.

45:43.441 --> 45:45.875
- Then why do you blame him?
- You are a Christian.

45:45.877 --> 45:47.176
No, I'm just speaking
for this man.

45:47.178 --> 45:49.045
You argue like the missionaries!

45:49.047 --> 45:50.580
Well, that's what you think
and I can't do anything--

45:50.582 --> 45:53.182
This man will write
in his newspaper

45:53.184 --> 45:56.252
that you are fools
and ignorant farmers.

45:56.254 --> 45:57.920
That is not true--

45:57.922 --> 45:59.589
Then he will pressurize
the government

45:59.591 --> 46:01.357
to take the leper woman back.

46:01.359 --> 46:04.293
- That's not true at all! That--
- We have to stop him!

46:04.295 --> 46:06.763
We have to stop him
writing these lies!

46:06.765 --> 46:08.564
[speaking in foreign language]

46:08.566 --> 46:10.700
[clamoring]

46:11.970 --> 46:13.636
Just wait! Listen!

46:13.638 --> 46:15.471
Listen to what I've written
in my research!

46:15.473 --> 46:17.039
Just listen to me!

46:20.378 --> 46:22.745
"The traditional lifestyle
in the villages

46:22.747 --> 46:25.381
is disintegrating.

46:25.383 --> 46:27.917
Farmers are leaving
their lands and families.

46:27.919 --> 46:29.786
Why?"

46:29.788 --> 46:31.754
- The missionaries.
- Yes.

46:31.756 --> 46:33.623
"The missionaries have been
operating out of India

46:33.625 --> 46:35.792
for hundreds of years now

46:35.794 --> 46:38.494
and they've undermined thousands
of years of traditions.

46:38.496 --> 46:40.797
Converts to Christianity

46:40.799 --> 46:42.999
no longer respect feast days,

46:43.001 --> 46:45.268
make sacrifices
to the village Gods

46:45.270 --> 46:47.103
or submit
to the village elders."

46:47.105 --> 46:49.071
[indistinct chatter]

46:50.809 --> 46:54.610
"No wonder there is
social disintegration, failure.

46:54.612 --> 46:57.513
But do the missionaries
ever get the blame for this?"

46:57.515 --> 46:59.582
[indistinct chatter]

47:01.085 --> 47:03.519
"Exactly.
No one ever blames them.

47:05.456 --> 47:07.824
The missionaries
divide and conquer

47:07.826 --> 47:10.860
causing the people of India
to fight with each other.

47:10.862 --> 47:12.328
But this is like
attacking the chickens

47:12.330 --> 47:13.996
when they do not lay eggs."

47:13.998 --> 47:15.731
[laughter]

47:17.602 --> 47:19.969
"It is the snake
who's disturbing the chicken.

47:19.971 --> 47:21.771
That must be destroyed.

47:21.773 --> 47:23.940
When a snake takes the chicken
or the eggs,

47:23.942 --> 47:26.275
you do not attack the chicken,

47:26.277 --> 47:29.278
but you lay in wait for
the snake and cut off its head.

47:33.151 --> 47:35.852
The people of India
need to protect their tradition

47:35.854 --> 47:38.487
by cutting off
the heads of these snakes,

47:38.489 --> 47:40.790
the true enemies
of a successful India."

47:45.330 --> 47:48.331
[indistinct chatter]

47:48.333 --> 47:50.066
Yes! Yes!

47:51.236 --> 47:53.302
Yes! Yes!

47:53.304 --> 47:55.504
[indistinct chatter]

47:55.506 --> 47:58.241
We need to cut the head
of the snake!

48:07.585 --> 48:09.418
<i> Manav: At the time,</i>
<i> I was merely relieved</i>

48:09.420 --> 48:12.722
<i> to have escaped a beating,</i>
<i> at least.</i>

48:12.724 --> 48:16.525
<i> I don't know how far</i>
<i> they would have gone.</i>

48:16.527 --> 48:18.094
<i> I also had no idea</i>

48:18.096 --> 48:20.162
<i> that my words may have</i>
<i> a consequence.</i>

48:22.367 --> 48:26.068
<i> If only I'd known how far</i>
<i> my-- my random thought</i>

48:26.070 --> 48:29.038
<i> had gone in the mind</i>
<i> of that man.</i>

48:29.040 --> 48:31.240
<i> That I didn't know.</i>

48:49.193 --> 48:51.460
[cock cawing]

48:53.865 --> 48:55.865
[instrumental music]

48:55.867 --> 48:57.833
[baby crying]

49:32.236 --> 49:33.469
Shanti: Manav.

49:35.273 --> 49:38.007
- I'm sorry.
- Shh, shh, shh.

49:38.009 --> 49:40.009
It's not your fault.

49:41.446 --> 49:43.846
You did not cause this.
Understand?

49:45.516 --> 49:47.850
Rest now. Hmm.

50:07.772 --> 50:10.740
[dramatic music]

51:05.263 --> 51:07.897
Graham: Gotta go
to a jungle camp.

51:07.899 --> 51:10.132
It's out in Manoharpur village.

51:48.106 --> 51:50.739
[speaking in foreign language]

51:50.741 --> 51:53.709
[bell tolling]

51:57.748 --> 51:59.682
[speaking in foreign language]

52:06.224 --> 52:08.324
Well, I didn't expect
to see you out here.

52:10.795 --> 52:13.462
- Research.
- Well, this is how we do it.

52:15.766 --> 52:17.299
Ah! Ah!

52:20.238 --> 52:22.671
[groaning]

52:26.410 --> 52:28.577
[children chattering]

52:39.957 --> 52:41.790
Timothy: Run! Keep going!

52:41.792 --> 52:44.760
[indistinct chatter]

52:54.338 --> 52:57.006
[screaming]

52:57.008 --> 52:58.908
[speaking in foreign language]

53:09.554 --> 53:11.554
Good boy. Careful.

53:16.027 --> 53:17.726
Mr. Staines...

53:18.863 --> 53:20.863
why do you do this?

53:33.878 --> 53:36.312
I was 16
when I first saw this picture.

53:38.316 --> 53:41.050
Couldn't get it out of my mind.

53:41.052 --> 53:43.786
Boy my age from here
with no hope.

53:48.859 --> 53:50.593
You have no fear.

53:51.996 --> 53:53.529
That boy you picked up
the other--

53:53.531 --> 53:55.331
Uh, the first time
I was so scared,

53:55.333 --> 53:58.334
I nearly threw up.

53:58.336 --> 54:00.569
Or maybe it was just the curry.

54:00.571 --> 54:02.504
[laughs]

54:02.506 --> 54:05.174
Sundar. You know, the old guy.

54:05.176 --> 54:08.043
<i> He was the first.</i>

54:08.045 --> 54:10.012
<i> He was just trying to get back</i>
<i> to his village</i>

54:10.014 --> 54:12.448
<i> to see his son one last time</i>
<i> before he died.</i>

54:12.450 --> 54:14.750
[mellow music]

54:18.055 --> 54:20.990
God wouldn't let me ride on.

54:25.630 --> 54:27.796
And these days,
we have a medical cure.

54:31.702 --> 54:33.702
You could do it, you know.

54:41.412 --> 54:44.380
[speaking in foreign language]

55:00.631 --> 55:02.631
Philip: Come on, Laki. Come on!

55:04.468 --> 55:06.335
You can put your hands down.

55:06.337 --> 55:08.771
The government
provides medicine now.

55:08.773 --> 55:11.707
- Yup.
- We don't need you anymore.

55:13.244 --> 55:15.477
Why do you stay?

55:15.479 --> 55:18.447
It's my calling.

55:18.449 --> 55:22.184
And for people like Sundar.
He's got no family.

55:22.186 --> 55:24.753
That's his karma.

55:24.755 --> 55:27.489
You can call the leprosy karma,

55:27.491 --> 55:30.125
but the way we treat him...

55:30.127 --> 55:32.161
that's not his karma.

55:32.163 --> 55:35.130
People are afraid of the curse.

55:35.132 --> 55:38.367
So fear, unfounded fear...

55:39.837 --> 55:42.104
prevents the people
from doing good.

55:44.208 --> 55:47.676
And what you do is good?

55:47.678 --> 55:49.345
Graham: I hope so.

55:51.148 --> 55:54.383
And your good converts people.

55:56.721 --> 55:58.187
Sometimes.

56:02.193 --> 56:05.227
My wife's in hospital.

56:05.229 --> 56:08.230
The doctors advise a transfer
to the city for surgery.

56:10.034 --> 56:12.034
We cannot afford to pay.

56:20.411 --> 56:23.579
What if I become a... Christian?

56:32.757 --> 56:34.923
That would be
a forced conversion.

56:37.995 --> 56:40.562
So fear...

56:40.564 --> 56:42.765
unfounded fear prevents you.

56:46.337 --> 56:48.470
I'll pray about it.

56:54.845 --> 56:56.812
Philip: Come on, Laki! Come on!

57:00.618 --> 57:03.552
Come on, Laki! Come on, run!

57:03.554 --> 57:05.521
Laki! Come on!

57:05.523 --> 57:07.189
Faster, faster.

57:07.191 --> 57:08.891
I know you can do it!
You can make it!

57:08.893 --> 57:10.058
You're nearly there!

57:10.060 --> 57:12.194
Come on, run, run, run, run!

57:12.196 --> 57:15.264
Keep going! Come on!

57:15.266 --> 57:17.433
The kids are doing good.

57:17.435 --> 57:20.436
[cheering]

57:20.438 --> 57:22.971
Could be an inducement.

57:22.973 --> 57:24.373
[chuckles]

57:28.646 --> 57:31.880
You know, Jesus healed
ten lepers once.

57:31.882 --> 57:34.783
How many you think
came back to thank Him?

57:34.785 --> 57:37.586
- Not all?
- One.

57:37.588 --> 57:39.788
But he still healed them all.

57:41.559 --> 57:43.525
So will you help my wife?

57:47.765 --> 57:49.965
God's the one
that can really help.

57:49.967 --> 57:52.067
Why don't you ask Him?

57:53.270 --> 57:55.003
I'm asking you.

57:58.442 --> 58:01.410
Like I said, I'll pray about it.

58:05.282 --> 58:08.350
Why don't you check out
the preaching? Good crowd today.

58:15.993 --> 58:18.327
I promise to come back
and thank you.

58:21.932 --> 58:24.600
- Hi, dad.
- Hey, boys.

58:24.602 --> 58:26.201
- Hi.
- I saw you out there.

58:26.203 --> 58:28.770
- Are you done today?
- Yeah, you did real well.

58:28.772 --> 58:30.739
- Thanks, dad. Thanks.
- Hm.

58:37.014 --> 58:40.015
[dramatic music]

58:48.292 --> 58:49.691
Mahendra?

58:51.061 --> 58:53.128
Mahendra: Eh.

58:53.130 --> 58:54.863
Journalist.

58:54.865 --> 58:57.733
What are you doing here
in Manoharpur?

58:57.735 --> 58:59.067
[sighs]

59:05.409 --> 59:07.809
Hey, don't be nervous.

59:07.811 --> 59:09.311
No, I...

59:09.313 --> 59:11.880
Just surprised to see you here,
that's all.

59:11.882 --> 59:14.550
Are you sure?
You are not Christian?

59:17.922 --> 59:20.322
What if I was?

59:20.324 --> 59:24.593
Because you only said
we shouldn't blame chickens.

59:25.930 --> 59:27.930
[speaking in foreign language]

59:32.937 --> 59:35.237
Why are you here though?

59:35.239 --> 59:38.707
We are performing a drama.
Want to come?

59:38.709 --> 59:41.677
[intense music]

59:44.915 --> 59:46.915
[speaking in foreign language]

1:00:43.907 --> 1:00:46.875
[no audio]

1:01:26.216 --> 1:01:27.683
[cycle bell rings]

1:01:29.219 --> 1:01:31.219
[indistinct chatter]

1:01:34.692 --> 1:01:36.758
Got it? Real good. Okay.

1:01:47.738 --> 1:01:49.304
- Hi.
- Hi.

1:01:51.175 --> 1:01:53.842
You here for the evening dance,
or just more research?

1:01:53.844 --> 1:01:56.545
Timothy: Okay, I got it.
I'm getting it.

1:01:56.547 --> 1:01:58.080
Mr. Staines.

1:02:01.485 --> 1:02:04.720
Do you ever worry that you might
be in danger out here?

1:02:04.722 --> 1:02:07.389
Yeah. Diarrhea.

1:02:07.391 --> 1:02:08.423
[blows raspberry]

1:02:08.425 --> 1:02:10.826
[laughs]

1:02:10.828 --> 1:02:13.995
Have you heard of a man
called Mahendra?

1:02:16.200 --> 1:02:17.632
Which one?

1:02:21.071 --> 1:02:24.339
He doesn't like missionaries.

1:02:24.341 --> 1:02:27.075
Being a missionary
is not a popularity contest.

1:02:28.846 --> 1:02:32.080
- You heard something?
- I'm not certain.

1:02:35.519 --> 1:02:38.587
Only two things in life
are certain, mate.

1:02:38.589 --> 1:02:41.556
Death and taxes.

1:02:41.558 --> 1:02:43.692
It's worth being prepared
for both.

1:02:48.632 --> 1:02:51.900
Your wife just had a baby?

1:02:51.902 --> 1:02:54.469
Don't work so hard.
Get back to your family.

1:02:55.773 --> 1:02:56.972
I will.

1:02:59.543 --> 1:03:01.343
See you later.

1:03:14.925 --> 1:03:17.893
[siren blaring]

1:03:29.473 --> 1:03:31.473
[indistinct chatter]

1:03:37.915 --> 1:03:39.381
Where's she?

1:03:43.821 --> 1:03:45.220
Shanti: Manav.

1:03:47.624 --> 1:03:48.890
Shanti.

1:03:50.360 --> 1:03:53.061
The bed was needed for a patient
who had paid.

1:03:56.633 --> 1:03:59.801
- I'm so sorry.
- It's fine.

1:03:59.803 --> 1:04:01.770
I will be right back.

1:04:06.109 --> 1:04:09.110
Excuse me. Haven't the bills
been paid for bed number 6?

1:04:15.152 --> 1:04:17.552
- No.
- I was told they have been.

1:04:21.859 --> 1:04:23.225
Here.

1:04:24.995 --> 1:04:26.361
And this.

1:04:26.363 --> 1:04:29.364
[telephone ringing]

1:04:32.736 --> 1:04:34.703
- Hello.
Manav: Sir, Banerjee.

1:04:34.705 --> 1:04:36.404
Where have you been, Banerjee?

1:04:36.406 --> 1:04:38.306
Sir, my wife was left out there
on a stretcher, sir.

1:04:38.308 --> 1:04:39.841
Why are you telling me?

1:04:39.843 --> 1:04:41.243
Sir, you said
you'll pay the hospital.

1:04:41.245 --> 1:04:44.079
I paid.
She's young. She'll be fine.

1:04:44.081 --> 1:04:46.147
Sir, I can't work
if my wife isn't cared for.

1:04:46.149 --> 1:04:47.849
Here's a thought.

1:04:47.851 --> 1:04:49.584
If you're spending time
with her,

1:04:49.586 --> 1:04:51.019
why should I pay the hospital?

1:04:51.021 --> 1:04:52.354
Sir, I'm working, sir.

1:04:52.356 --> 1:04:54.656
I'm paying you to convert,
Banerjee.

1:04:54.658 --> 1:04:55.924
To get some real evidence.

1:04:55.926 --> 1:04:56.992
Sir, but if I find evidence,

1:04:56.994 --> 1:04:58.260
evidence is evidence, right?

1:04:58.262 --> 1:05:01.196
You do what I'm paying you for

1:05:01.198 --> 1:05:02.564
and I look after your wife.

1:05:02.566 --> 1:05:03.665
Sir, but...

1:05:03.667 --> 1:05:05.267
Hello? Sir?

1:05:16.013 --> 1:05:18.847
[chuckles] Let's go to bed.

1:05:18.849 --> 1:05:20.515
-<i> Namaskar. </i>
-<i> Namaskar.</i>

1:05:22.019 --> 1:05:24.119
Come on, boys.

1:05:24.121 --> 1:05:26.154
Alright, boys,
ready to call it a day?

1:05:29.960 --> 1:05:32.761
[speaking in foreign language]

1:05:32.763 --> 1:05:34.863
[indistinct chatter]

1:05:41.138 --> 1:05:43.772
Are you sure you have nothing
on a Mahendra?

1:05:44.975 --> 1:05:47.442
If he's not dead, I don't know.

1:05:49.880 --> 1:05:51.212
See, I'm sure he's trouble.

1:05:51.214 --> 1:05:54.582
Oh, is he also
converting illegally?

1:05:54.584 --> 1:05:57.719
I saw him buying alcohol.
I saw him at Manoharpur--

1:05:57.721 --> 1:06:00.155
That area is not
under our jurisdiction.

1:06:00.157 --> 1:06:04.793
- Who's it under?
- Um, um, Thakurmunda.

1:06:04.795 --> 1:06:07.595
- Can you call them?
- And tell them what?

1:06:07.597 --> 1:06:11.599
J-- just to check on him.
I'm sure he's trouble.

1:06:11.601 --> 1:06:14.202
You, you are the troublemaker.

1:06:15.739 --> 1:06:17.806
I can give you a bed
for the night.

1:06:19.276 --> 1:06:21.242
You want? Huh?

